Starts a simple file-serving HTTP server in a directory, at an OS-assigned port,
and opens the default web browser to the root URL.

Requirements:

 * Python 2.5 or greater. Works with Py3k.

Usage:

    $ ./quickserver
    Serving HTTP on 0.0.0.0 port 61209 ...
    http://0.0.0.0:61209/
    127.0.0.1 - - [19/Jun/2014 17:21:56] "GET / HTTP/1.1" 200 -
    [ YOUR BROWSER MAGICALLY HAS OPENED A NEW TAB DIRECTLY TO THIS URL ]